column1: #Text=: Individually , what is your opinion of some of your fellow candidates for the Republican Party presidential nomination , notably Mitt Romney , Michele Bachmann , Ron Paul and Herman Cain ? Why do you feel you would be a better nominee for the party than any of them ?
#Text=Martin : I have occasionally written brief profiles and short commentaries on some of my opponents .
#Text=Those columns are posted on my blogs .
#Text=I refer you to those comments and any that appear in the future ( as no doubt they will ) .
#Text=How often do you campaign , and how has the campaign been received by people you meet ?
#Text=I would say I have received an extraordinarily warm and positive response wherever I have campaigned .
#Text=I place my campaign in the top 10 , i.e. among the top 10 Republican presidential candidates nationally .
#Text=While most of the media attention is focused on the top 5 , some of the top 5 are tottering and will not survive .
#Text=: Which other candidates would you also place in the top 10 ?
#Text=Martin : the usual ones , so long as they have actually announced .
#Text=: Have you received any notable endorsements ?
#Text=Martin : I receive the “ endorsement ” of ordinary Americans every day in my campaign .
#Text=That is the only endorsement that counts .
#Text=Do you feel you can still win the nomination despite not receiving an invitation to any of the presidential debates ?
#Text=Martin : I have a game plan and strategy to try to win , and we are executing that game plan well .
#Text=I am very satisfied with the progress of the campaign .
#Text=Actually , by excluding me from some of the debates to date , the media have been the losers .
#Text=Some of the candidates they are showcasing are imploding , thereby brightening my prospects to move up on the presidential leader board .
#Text=In your estimation approximately how many supporters does your campaign have ?
#Text=Martin : I ca n’t give an exact number , nor would I if we tallied supporters that way .
#Text=But it clear my campaign is gaining altitude and other candidates are faltering .
#Text=We are executing our game plan ; others rather obviously are not .
#Text=If you do not win the Republican nomination , would you consider running for a third party ' s nomination ?
#Text=On his campaign website , Martin describes himself as a supporter of the Second Amendment to the United States Constitution in opposition to stringent gun control .
#Text=He opposes Cap and Trade legislation and mandated health care coverage .
#Text=He identifies himself as a proponent of the First Amendment to the United States Constitution and a " corruption fighter " .
